just not a... safe place.

31:35.259 --> 31:37.784
And besides,
I'm not sure it's appropriate

31:37.895 --> 31:41.126
for your father to bring you
on a business trip.

31:41.231 --> 31:42.664
Appropriate for who?

31:42.766 --> 31:44.734
What?

31:44.835 --> 31:47.133
Mom, is it possible that
you're taking the frustration

31:47.237 --> 31:49.102
of your failed marriage out on me?

31:50.174 --> 31:52.642
Excuse me?

31:52.743 --> 31:55.007
This California trip seems like
a great learning opportunity

31:55.112 --> 31:57.910
and a chance for me
to get to know my father.

31:58.015 --> 31:59.744
But if you think it's more important

31:59.850 --> 32:01.715
to use me to channel your frustration

32:01.819 --> 32:03.719
against the man you no longer love,

32:03.821 --> 32:05.482
I'll understand.

32:10.527 --> 32:12.461
How'd you convince her?

32:12.563 --> 32:14.758
It was an argument,
not a negotiation.

32:14.865 --> 32:16.492
That's my boy.

33:02.813 --> 33:04.474
Nick?

33:04.581 --> 33:06.708
Nick, Jack, Jeff's assistant. Hey.

33:06.817 --> 33:09.081
How was your flight?
Are you jet-lagged at all?

33:09.186 --> 33:10.881
It's, like, 2:00 in D.C.
Right now.

33:10.988 --> 33:12.455
You know what?
Take some vitamin B.

33:12.556 --> 33:13.784
Jeff swears by it- in fact,

33:13.891 --> 33:15.552
I'm gonna hook you up
with an injection.

33:15.659 --> 33:17.058
Who's this with you?
How are you, dude? What's going on?

33:17.161 --> 33:18.253
You guys ever been to L.A. Before?

33:18.362 --> 33:20.193
You want to head back
to Jeffâ€™s office?

33:20.297 --> 33:22.663
In fact, we probably should-
He's a punctual being.

33:22.766 --> 33:25.599
We actually had some problems at first
with the exterior mirrored glass.

33:25.702 --> 33:28.262
The reflection of the sun was causing
head-on collisions on Wilshire.

33:28.372 --> 33:29.964
Oh, is everybody all right?

33:30.073 --> 33:32.234
Yeah, they got three-picture deals
at Paramount- I'm sure they'll live.

33:32.342 --> 33:33.570
- It's a nice building.
- Yeah?

33:33.677 --> 33:35.542
Hey, tell Jeff you think so, okay?

33:35.646 --> 33:38.171
'Cause he just put a lot
of himself into this building.

33:38.282 --> 33:41.718
And you know something?
It really shows.

33:41.819 --> 33:43.377
What's up, Hiroshi?

33:43.487 --> 33:47.253
Keep going- that sand's
not gonna rake itself.

33:47.357 --> 33:49.382
All right, come here,
this is my favorite part.

33:49.493 --> 33:52.724
That one right there?
It's $7,000.

33:52.830 --> 33:54.855
- $7,000 for a fish?
- Yep.

33:54.965 --> 33:56.865
Kind of makes you want
to stop eating sushi,

33:56.967 --> 33:58.594
but I guess you kind of have to.

33:58.702 --> 34:00.533
Hey, you see that
big white one right there?

34:00.637 --> 34:03.401
Swear to you- $12,000,
gift from Oprah.

34:03.507 --> 34:07.307
It's a Chamberlain- office-warming gift
from Matthew McConaughey.

34:07.411 --> 34:08.775
Generous gift.

34:08.879 --> 34:10.904
Yeah. Right!

34:11.014 --> 34:13.847
Don't get me wrong, Matthew is
a tremendously talented individual

34:13.951 --> 34:15.440
and an extremely decent human being,

34:15.552 --> 34:18.077
however, before Jeff
took him on, he was a face.

34:18.188 --> 34:19.416
Now he's a name.

34:23.060 --> 34:25.960
Do you hear that?

34:29.199 --> 34:30.530
No.

34:31.601 --> 34:33.831
Exactly.

34:42.713 --> 34:44.078
Hey, Neal.

34:44.181 --> 34:46.445
Neal, I'm gonna impale
your mom on a spike,

34:46.550 --> 34:49.212
and I'm gonna feed her dead body
to my dog with syphilis.

34:49.319 --> 34:51.081
Aw, Jack, you got me!

34:51.188 --> 34:52.849
That guy!

34:52.956 --> 34:55.652
It's an inside joke.

34:55.759 --> 34:58.023
So, as you can see,

34:58.128 --> 35:00.323
Jeff just really loves Asian shit.

35:00.430 --> 35:02.159
Uh, Candace, is he ready?

35:02.266 --> 35:03.927
- Mm-hmm.
- Fantastic.

35:04.034 --> 35:06.298
Okay, Joey,
I'm gonna bring your dad in now.

35:06.403 --> 35:08.428
Is there anything I can get
you while you're waiting,

35:08.538 --> 35:10.733
like an orange juice
or a coffee or a Red Bull?

35:10.841 --> 35:13.241
- No, thanks.
- Okay.

35:15.746 --> 35:17.714
Wow, it's a great office.

35:17.814 --> 35:19.805
Yeah. Jeff basically designed
the whole thing.

35:19.917 --> 35:21.817
The architect just made the drawings.

35:21.919 --> 35:24.285
Jack, stop it.

35:24.388 --> 35:25.685
Next you're gonna be telling him

35:25.789 --> 35:27.279
what position I played
for the Bruins.

35:27.391 --> 35:28.341
Quarterback.

35:28.441 --> 35:29.654
Jeff Megall.

35:29.760 --> 35:30.988
Nick Naylor.

35:31.094 --> 35:33.324
Mr. Naylor's here to see
if we can't get cigarettes

35:33.430 --> 35:35.955
- into the hands of somebody
other than the usual RAVs. - Sure.

35:36.066 --> 35:38.557
- RAVs?
- Russians, Arabs and Villains.

35:38.669 --> 35:40.398
Oh, well, then yes, I guess
that is why I'm here.

35:40.504 --> 35:42.699
Good. I think we can help.

35:42.806 --> 35:44.899
Jeff invented product placement.

35:45.008 --> 35:46.976
I feel I have to ask, uh...

35:47.077 --> 35:50.069
Are you concerned at
all about the, um...

35:50.180 --> 35:51.738
about the health element?

35:51.848 --> 35:54.715
I'm not a doctor, I'm a facilitator.

35:54.818 --> 35:56.080
I bring creative people together.

35:56.186 --> 35:58.381
Whatever information there is,
exists, it's out there.

35:58.488 --> 35:59.682
People will decide for themselves.

35:59.790 --> 36:02.224
They should. It's not
my role to decide for them.

36:02.326 --> 36:04.226
It'd be morally presumptuous.

36:04.328 --> 36:06.888
<i>I could learn a lot</i>
<i>from this man.</i>

36:06.997 --> 36:09.363
Now, what we need is
a smoking role model,

36:09.466 --> 36:10.433
a real winner.

36:10.533 --> 36:12.195
Indiana Jones meets Jerry Maguire.

36:12.302 --> 36:13.360
Right, on two packs a day.

36:13.470 --> 36:15.495
Only he can't live
in contemporary society.

36:15.605 --> 36:16.555
Why not?

36:16.655 --> 36:18.597
The health issue's way too prevalent.

36:18.709 --> 36:20.643
People would constantly
be asking the character

36:20.744 --> 36:23.008
why he's smoking-
and that should go unsaid.

36:23.113 --> 36:25.047
How do you feel about the future?

36:25.148 --> 36:27.343
The future?

36:27.451 --> 36:29.180
Yeah, after the health thing's
blown over.

36:29.286 --> 36:30.617
A world
where smokers and nonsmokers

36:30.721 --> 36:32.120
live together in perfect harmony.

36:32.222 --> 36:34.588
Sony has a futuristic sci-fi movie
they're looking to make.

36:34.691 --> 36:36.625
<i>Message From Sector Six.</i>

36:36.727 --> 36:38.752
All takes place in a space station.

36:38.862 --> 36:40.727
They're actively looking
for some cofinancing.

36:40.831 --> 36:42.298
So cigarettes in space?

36:42.399 --> 36:44.526
It's the final frontier, Nick.

36:44.634 --> 36:46.625
But wouldn't they blow up
in an all-oxygen environment?

36:47.704 --> 36:49.433
Probably.

36:49.539 --> 36:52.133
But it's an easy fix-
one line of dialogue:

36:52.242 --> 36:54.210
"Thank God we invented the..."
you know,

36:54.311 --> 36:55.608
whatever device.

36:55.712 --> 36:57.577
Brad Pitt.

36:57.681 --> 36:59.239
Catherine Zeta-Jones.

36:59.349 --> 37:00.748
They've just finished ravishing

37:00.851 --> 37:03.445
each other's bodies
for the first time.

37:03.553 --> 37:05.578
They lie naked, suspended in air

37:05.689 --> 37:07.122
underneath the heavens.

37:07.224 --> 37:09.590
Pitt lights up.

37:09.693 --> 37:11.422
He starts blowing smoke rings
all around

37:11.528 --> 37:13.325
Catherine's naked, flawless body,

37:13.430 --> 37:16.593
as the galaxies go whizzing
by over the glass-domed ceiling.

37:16.700 --> 37:18.759
Now, tell me that
doesn't work for you.

37:18.869 --> 37:20.166
I'd see that movie.

37:20.270 --> 37:21.532
I'd buy the goddamn DVD.

37:21.638 --> 37:24.334
You know, if the academy
didn't send them to me for free.

37:24.441 --> 37:25.908
You know,

37:26.009 --> 37:28.170
you guys ought to think
about designing a cigarette

37:28.278 --> 37:30.007
to be released simultaneously
with the movie.

37:30.113 --> 37:31.671
Sector Sixes.

37:31.782 --> 37:33.340
No one's ever done it
with a cigarette.

37:33.450 --> 37:34.576
Wow.

37:34.684 --> 37:36.584
Well, where do we go from here?

37:36.686 --> 37:39.519
You enjoy the rest of your day
in L.A. With your son

37:39.623 --> 37:41.557
while I find out
the answers to these questions.

37:41.658 --> 37:44.286
Hey, where can I get
a bite to eat with my son?

37:44.394 --> 37:45.918
You ought to try Nobu's new place.

37:46.029 --> 37:48.429
- He only serves food that's white.
- Oh, great.

37:49.699 --> 37:51.929
<i>So, you go to an office,</i>

37:52.035 --> 37:54.663
<i>then you go on TV</i>
<i>and talk about cigarettes.</i>

37:54.771 --> 37:56.602
<i>Then you fly out to L.A.</i>

37:56.706 --> 37:59.174
To talk to some guy who
works with movie stars.

37:59.276 --> 38:02.575
- What is that?
- That's my job; I'm a lobbyist.

38:02.679 --> 38:05.341
I know, but did you study to do that?

38:05.449 --> 38:07.940
No. No, I just kind of figured it out.

38:08.051 --> 38:10.144
Then can't anyone just do that?

38:10.253 --> 38:14.189
No, it, uh, requires a...

38:14.291 --> 38:18.022
a moral flexibility
that goes beyond most people.

38:19.129 --> 38:21.962
Do I have flexible morals?

38:22.065 --> 38:24.761
Well, let's say
you became a lawyer, right?

38:24.868 --> 38:26.495
And you were asked
to defend a murderer.

38:26.603 --> 38:28.127
Worse than that- a child murderer.

38:28.238 --> 38:29.535
Now,

38:29.639 --> 38:32.631
the law states that every person
deserves a fair trial.

38:32.742 --> 38:34.835
Would you defend them?

38:34.945 --> 38:36.640
I don't know.
I guess every person

38:36.746 --> 38:38.577
- deserves a fair defense.
- Yeah, well,

38:38.682 --> 38:40.809
so do multinational corporations.

38:40.917 --> 38:44.216
So, what happens when you're wrong?

38:44.321 --> 38:45.982
Well, Joey, I'm never wrong.

38:46.089 --> 38:47.556
But you can't always be right.

38:47.657 --> 38:50.592
Well, if it's your job to be right,
then you're never wrong.

38:50.694 --> 38:52.889
<i>But what if you are wrong?</i>

38:52.996 --> 38:55.157
Okay, let's say that
you're defending chocolate

38:55.265 --> 38:56.596
and I'm defending vanilla.

38:56.700 --> 38:59.100
Now, if I were to say to you,

38:59.202 --> 39:02.103
"Vanilla's the best flavor
ice cream," you'd say?

39:02.205 --> 39:04.264
- "No, chocolate is."
- Exactly.

39:04.374 --> 39:05.966
But you can't win that argument.

39:06.076 --> 39:08.636
So, I'll ask you-
So you think chocolate

39:08.745 --> 39:11.543
is the end-all and be-all
of ice cream, do you?

39:11.648 --> 39:13.707
It's the best ice cream;
I wouldn't order any other.

39:13.817 --> 39:15.717
Oh. So it's all chocolate
for you, is it?

39:15.819 --> 39:17.411
Yes, chocolate is all I need.

39:17.521 --> 39:18.818
Well, I need more than chocolate.

39:18.922 --> 39:20.913
And for that matter,
I need more than vanilla.

39:21.024 --> 39:22.787
I believe that we need
freedom and choice

39:22.893 --> 39:25.384
when it comes to our ice cream,
and that, Joey Naylor,

39:25.495 --> 39:27.019
that is the definition of liberty.

39:27.130 --> 39:29.064
But that's not what
we're talking about.

39:29.166 --> 39:31.566
<i>Ah, but that's what</i>
<i>I'm talking about.</i>

39:31.668 --> 39:34.603
- But... you didn't prove that vanilla's the best.
- I didn't have to.

39:34.704 --> 39:37.537
I proved that you're wrong-
and if you're wrong, I'm right.

39:37.641 --> 39:38.624
But you still didn't

39:38.724 --> 39:39.766
convince me.

39:39.876 --> 39:41.207
'Cause I'm not after you.

39:41.311 --> 39:44.610
I'm after them.

40:00.697 --> 40:02.164
Hello?

40:02.265 --> 40:04.165
Thought I'd give you a little update.

40:04.267 --> 40:06.235
Jeff. You still at the office?

40:06.336 --> 40:08.861
Do you know what time it is
in Tokyo right now?

40:08.972 --> 40:10.735
- No.
- 4:00 p.m. Tomorrow.

40:10.840 --> 40:12.637
It's the future, Nick.

40:13.843 --> 40:15.572
Anyway, for Pitt to smoke,

40:15.679 --> 40:17.909
it's $10 million;
for the pair, it's 25.

40:18.014 --> 40:21.177
25?! Usually when I buy two
of something, I get a discount.

40:21.284 --> 40:22.478
What's the extra five for?

40:22.586 --> 40:23.746
Synergy.

40:23.853 --> 40:26.617
These are not stupid people;
they got it right away.

40:26.723 --> 40:28.953
Pitt and Zeta-Jones lighting up
after some cosmic fucking

40:29.059 --> 40:31.527
in the bubble suite's
gonna sell a lot of cigarettes.

40:31.628 --> 40:33.061
Well, for that kind of money,

40:33.163 --> 40:35.063
my people will expect
some very serious smoking.

40:35.165 --> 40:36.655
Can Brad blow smoke rings?

40:36.766 --> 40:38.165
I don't have that information.

40:38.268 --> 40:39.963
Well, for $25 million,
we'd want smoke rings.

40:40.070 --> 40:41.560
Oh, one other thing-
you'll be cofinancing

40:41.671 --> 40:43.605
the picture
with the Sultan of Glutan.

40:43.707 --> 40:44.901
The Sultan of Glutan?

40:45.008 --> 40:47.033
The one who massacred
and enslaved his own people?

40:47.143 --> 40:49.634
Aren't they calling him
the Hitler of the South Pacific?

40:49.746 --> 40:52.180
No, I can't speak to that-
All my dealings with him,

40:52.282 --> 40:54.011
he's been a very reasonable
and sensitive guy.

40:54.117 --> 40:55.345
He's fun. You'll like him.

40:55.452 --> 40:56.646
I better run it by my people.

40:56.753 --> 40:57.845
No problem.

40:57.954 --> 40:59.319
Oh, that's London calling.

40:59.422 --> 41:01.549
7:00 a.m. In the Old Empire.

41:01.658 --> 41:03.216
Jeff, when do you sleep?

41:03.326 --> 41:04.554
Sunday.

42:06.690 --> 42:09.181
- Operator.
- Yeah, my light is blinking.

42:09.292 --> 42:12.523
- There's a package downstairs for you.
- Okay, send it up.

42:15.065 --> 42:18.262
Captain, I'm sitting in front
of an open briefcase.

42:18.368 --> 42:20.393
I don't suppose this is a raise.

42:20.503 --> 42:24.303
Now, Nick, do you know
who Lorne Lutch is?

42:24.407 --> 42:26.102
Yeah, of course.
He's the original Marlboro Man.

42:26.209 --> 42:28.677
<i>He's dying.</i>
<i>He was on Sally last week.</i>

42:28.778 --> 42:30.973
Not exactly our biggest fan.

42:31.081 --> 42:32.309
Well, the money's for him.

42:32.415 --> 42:35.043
Now, he has a ranch
out there in California.

42:35.151 --> 42:36.812
I want you to bring it to him.

42:36.920 --> 42:40.754
He's a cowboy, sir,
and cowboys don't like bribes.

42:40.857 --> 42:43.018
It's not a bribe. No, sir.

42:43.126 --> 42:45.890
You're going out there
on wings of angels, son.

42:45.995 --> 42:48.930
You mean we're just going
to give him the money?

42:49.032 --> 42:50.431
Well, I think Christ himself
would say,

42:50.533 --> 42:52.763
"That's mighty white of you boys."

42:52.869 --> 42:54.928
No gag agreement?

42:55.038 --> 42:57.438
Hopefully, he'll be so damn
overcome with gratitude

42:57.540 --> 42:59.872
<i>he'll... he'll have to shut up.</i>

43:10.620 --> 43:12.952
Hey, kiddo, I got to go do
a little bit more work

43:13.056 --> 43:14.148
this afternoon, all right?

43:14.257 --> 43:15.207
Can I come?

43:15.307 --> 43:16.691
No. Not this time.

43:16.793 --> 43:18.954
But I want to see what you do.

44:00.270 --> 44:01.862
You stay here, okay?

44:21.024 --> 44:23.584
What the fuck are you doing here?

44:23.693 --> 44:26.287
Uh... uh...

44:26.396 --> 44:28.091
Do you have a minute?

44:33.236 --> 44:34.897
What do you want?

44:35.004 --> 44:36.232
Dad!

44:36.339 --> 44:37.465
Joey, get back in the car.

44:44.080 --> 44:46.071
Just want to talk.

44:47.417 --> 44:49.476
All right.

44:49.586 --> 44:51.053
Let's talk.

45:07.470 --> 45:09.904
Pearl, we got company.

45:12.542 --> 45:15.739
Mister, you got a lot of nerve
walking in here after...

45:15.845 --> 45:19.212
Honey, why don't you show
this young man some iced tea?

45:22.352 --> 45:23.842
I'll be right back, tiger.

45:40.270 --> 45:42.830
Saw you on...

45:42.939 --> 45:46.431
Weren't you on that TV show?

45:46.543 --> 45:49.341
Yeah. Yeah, that was me.

45:49.445 --> 45:53.006
You're lucky you made it
out of there alive.

45:53.116 --> 45:55.414
Yeah. Tobacco used to be
all over the television.

45:55.518 --> 45:59.511
Now TV is leading the witch hunt.

45:59.622 --> 46:01.487
Strange business.

46:01.591 --> 46:04.492
Last year, after I was diagnosed,

46:04.594 --> 46:10.123
flew east to attend the
annual stockholders' convention.

46:11.901 --> 46:13.869
Stood up and told them
I thought

46:13.970 --> 46:18.600
they ought to cut back
on their advertising.

46:18.708 --> 46:21.302
You know what your boss said to me?

46:24.547 --> 46:27.607
He said, "We're certainly sorry

46:27.717 --> 46:31.483
"to hear about your medical problem.

46:31.588 --> 46:35.024
"However, without
knowing more

46:35.124 --> 46:38.787
"of your medical history,

46:38.895 --> 46:40.988
we can't comment further."

46:43.566 --> 46:45.796
But then they tried to pretend

46:45.902 --> 46:47.631
I never worked for 'em.

46:49.572 --> 46:51.802
Yeah, I got the pay stubs.

46:51.908 --> 46:54.672
But, hell,
I was on the damn billboards.

46:56.412 --> 46:58.141
I never
even smoked

46:58.247 --> 47:00.272
Marlboro.

47:00.383 --> 47:02.851
I smoked Kools.

47:07.256 --> 47:10.384
You look like a nice-enough fella.

47:10.493 --> 47:12.791
What are you doing
working for these assholes?

47:14.697 --> 47:16.756
I'm good at it.

47:16.866 --> 47:18.094
Better at doing this

47:18.201 --> 47:19.862
than I ever was
at doing anything else.

47:19.969 --> 47:21.903
Aw, hell, son.

47:22.005 --> 47:24.565
I was good at shooting VC.

47:24.674 --> 47:26.642
I didn't make it my career.

47:28.945 --> 47:32.608
I suppose we all
got to pay the mortgage.

47:36.452 --> 47:38.613
Your dad always bring
you along like this?

47:38.721 --> 47:41.451
No. I live with my mom.

47:41.557 --> 47:43.286
He tell you why he's here today?

47:43.393 --> 47:47.227
He said that your husband
was the Marlboro Man.

47:48.831 --> 47:52.631
Yeah, well, not anymore.

47:52.735 --> 47:54.202
Hello.

47:54.303 --> 47:56.464
Yeah. Hey, can you hold on a second?

47:56.572 --> 48:00.668
You need anything else,
grab it out of the fridge.

48:00.777 --> 48:02.438
So I'm standing here
minding my own business,

48:02.545 --> 48:04.410
filling up pill bottles...

48:04.514 --> 48:10.419
So you're here to talk me
into shutting up?

48:12.288 --> 48:14.552
That what's in that case of yours?

48:14.657 --> 48:17.319
Yeah, basically.

48:18.528 --> 48:19.927
No, not basically.

48:20.029 --> 48:22.259
That's... that's exactly it.

48:24.367 --> 48:25.994
My dignity ain't for sale.

48:26.102 --> 48:28.570
It's not an offer.
It's a gift.

48:28.671 --> 48:29.797
Taxes have all been paid.

48:29.906 --> 48:32.636
You get to keep it
no matter what you do.

48:32.742 --> 48:34.175
The idea is that, somehow,

48:34.277 --> 48:36.905
your guilt will prevent you
from bad-mouthing us.

48:37.013 --> 48:38.810
Are you supposed to be

48:38.915 --> 48:40.610
telling me all that?

48:40.717 --> 48:43.242
No, sir. Just apologize,

48:43.352 --> 48:45.115
