01:17:57.038 --> 01:17:58.266
By, um...

01:17:58.372 --> 01:17:59.498
And specifically

01:17:59.607 --> 01:18:00.557
Mr...

01:18:00.657 --> 01:18:01.666
Um...

01:18:01.776 --> 01:18:03.368
Mr., uh, Nick Naylor.

01:18:03.478 --> 01:18:04.428
Nick Naylor?

01:18:04.528 --> 01:18:05.479
Thank you very much.

01:18:07.448 --> 01:18:08.398
<i>The current use</i>

01:18:08.498 --> 01:18:10.076
of words instead of imagery

01:18:10.184 --> 01:18:13.779
is an obvious move against
the non-English-speaking population

01:18:13.888 --> 01:18:15.355
of the United States.

01:18:15.456 --> 01:18:17.583
The skull and crossbones

01:18:17.692 --> 01:18:21.059
speak loudly in all languages.

01:18:21.162 --> 01:18:23.756
By not using it,
they're saying

01:18:23.865 --> 01:18:27.892
they want those who can't
read English to die.

01:18:28.002 --> 01:18:29.765
Hmm. Senor Herrera,

01:18:29.871 --> 01:18:32.704
could you clarify "they"?

01:18:32.807 --> 01:18:34.104
<i>Let it be known,</i>

01:18:34.208 --> 01:18:36.676
<i>the public beating</i>
<i>has not gone out of style.</i>

01:18:44.018 --> 01:18:46.179
Nick Naylor, please step forward.

01:18:55.897 --> 01:18:58.525
You go sit with him.

01:19:06.908 --> 01:19:09.900
Please state your name,
address and current occupation.

01:19:10.011 --> 01:19:11.137
My name is Nick Naylor.

01:19:11.245 --> 01:19:13.008
I live at 6000
Massachusetts Avenue

01:19:13.114 --> 01:19:15.014
and I am currently unemployed,

01:19:15.116 --> 01:19:17.243
but until recently,
I was the vice president

01:19:17.351 --> 01:19:18.841
of the Academy of Tobacco Studies.

01:19:18.953 --> 01:19:19.903
Mr. Naylor,

01:19:20.003 --> 01:19:23.412
as vice president
of the Academy

01:19:23.524 --> 01:19:25.492
of Tobacco Studies,
what was required of you?

01:19:25.593 --> 01:19:26.821
What did you do?

01:19:26.928 --> 01:19:30.420
I informed the public
of all the research performed

01:19:30.531 --> 01:19:32.522
in the investigation
on the effects of tobacco.

01:19:32.633 --> 01:19:33.759
Mm-hmm,
and what,

01:19:33.868 --> 01:19:36.428
so far,
has the Academy concluded

01:19:36.537 --> 01:19:38.971
in their investigation
into the effects of tobacco?

01:19:39.073 --> 01:19:41.337
Well, many things, actually.

01:19:41.442 --> 01:19:43.205
Why, just the other day
they uncovered evidence

01:19:43.311 --> 01:19:45.142
that smoking can offset
Parkinson's disease.

01:19:47.081 --> 01:19:48.309
I'm sure the health
community

01:19:48.416 --> 01:19:49.542
is thrilled.

01:19:49.650 --> 01:19:52.551
Mr. Naylor, who provides
the financial backing

01:19:52.653 --> 01:19:54.621
for the Academy of Tobacco Studies?

01:19:54.722 --> 01:19:57.987
Uh... Conglomerated Tobacco.

01:19:58.092 --> 01:19:59.787
That's the cigarette companies.

01:19:59.894 --> 01:20:01.953
For the most part, yes.

01:20:02.063 --> 01:20:04.964
Do you think that...

01:20:05.066 --> 01:20:07.034
might affect their priorities?

01:20:07.134 --> 01:20:08.465
No, just as I'm sure

01:20:08.569 --> 01:20:10.400
campaign contributions
don't affect yours.

01:20:10.504 --> 01:20:11.528
Oh.

01:20:13.507 --> 01:20:16.738
Senators, Mr. Naylor is not here
to testify on the goings-on

01:20:16.844 --> 01:20:18.641
of the Academy of Tobacco Studies.

01:20:18.746 --> 01:20:20.805
We're here to examine
the possibility

01:20:20.915 --> 01:20:22.314
of a warning logo on cigarettes.

01:20:22.416 --> 01:20:23.400
Now, Mr. Naylor,

01:20:23.500 --> 01:20:25.008
I have to ask you,
out of formality,

01:20:25.119 --> 01:20:27.087
do you believe that smoking
cigarettes, over time,

01:20:27.188 --> 01:20:30.419
can lead to lung cancer and
other respiratory conditions

01:20:30.524 --> 01:20:31.718
such as emphysema?

01:20:33.594 --> 01:20:35.084
Yes.

01:20:37.932 --> 01:20:38.882
In fact, I think you'd be
hard-pressed

01:20:38.982 --> 01:20:40.025
to find someone
who really believes

01:20:40.134 --> 01:20:42.102
that cigarettes are not
potentially harmful.

01:20:42.203 --> 01:20:44.433
I mean, show of hands,
who out here thinks

01:20:44.538 --> 01:20:46.028
- that cigarettes aren't dangerous...
- Mr. Naylor.

01:20:46.140 --> 01:20:49.268
There's no need for theatrics.

01:20:49.377 --> 01:20:51.937
Sir, I just don't see the point in a warning
label for something people already know.

01:20:52.046 --> 01:20:53.343
The warning symbol

01:20:53.447 --> 01:20:57.076
is a reminder, a reminder of the
dangers of smoking cigarettes.

01:20:57.184 --> 01:20:59.015
Well, if we want to remind
people of danger,

01:20:59.120 --> 01:21:00.644
why don't we slap
a skull and crossbones

01:21:00.755 --> 01:21:01.738
on all Boeing airplanes,

01:21:01.838 --> 01:21:03.255
Senator Lothridge?

01:21:03.357 --> 01:21:04.324
And all Fords, Senator Dupree?

01:21:04.424 --> 01:21:06.724
That is ridiculous.

01:21:06.827 --> 01:21:09.125
The death toll from airline
and automobile accidents

01:21:09.230 --> 01:21:11.289
doesn't even skim the surface
of cigarettes.

01:21:11.399 --> 01:21:12.457
They don't even compare.

01:21:12.566 --> 01:21:14.625
Oh, this from a senator
who calls Vermont home.

01:21:14.735 --> 01:21:16.862
I don't follow you, Mr. Naylor.

01:21:16.971 --> 01:21:18.632
Well, the real

01:21:18.739 --> 01:21:21.299
demonstrated number one killer
in America is cholesterol,

01:21:21.409 --> 01:21:22.409
and here comes
Senator Finistirre,

01:21:22.510 --> 01:21:24.740
whose fine state is,
I regret to say,

01:21:24.845 --> 01:21:27.871
clogging the nation's arteries
with Vermont cheddar cheese.

01:21:29.517 --> 01:21:32.247
If we want to talk numbers,
how about the millions of people

01:21:32.353 --> 01:21:33.337
dying of heart attacks.

01:21:33.437 --> 01:21:34.683
Perhaps Vermont cheddar

01:21:34.789 --> 01:21:37.155
should come
with a skull and crossbones.

01:21:37.258 --> 01:21:39.089
That is lud...

01:21:39.193 --> 01:21:40.177
The great state of Vermont

01:21:40.277 --> 01:21:41.819
will not apologize for its cheese.

01:21:41.929 --> 01:21:42.913
Mr. Naylor,

01:21:43.013 --> 01:21:44.487
we are here to discuss cigarettes.

01:21:44.598 --> 01:21:48.227
Not planes, not cars- cigarettes.

01:21:48.335 --> 01:21:50.997
Now, as we discussed earlier,
these warning labels

01:21:51.105 --> 01:21:54.302
are not for those who know, but
rather for those who don't know.

01:21:56.277 --> 01:21:58.268
What about the children?

01:21:58.379 --> 01:22:00.404
Gentlemen...

01:22:00.514 --> 01:22:02.448
it's called education.

01:22:02.550 --> 01:22:04.415
It doesn't come off the side
of a cigarette carton.

01:22:04.518 --> 01:22:05.576
It comes from our teachers,

01:22:05.686 --> 01:22:07.745
and more importantly, our parents.

01:22:07.855 --> 01:22:10.983
It is the job
of every parent

01:22:11.092 --> 01:22:14.721
to warn their children of all
the dangers of the world,

01:22:14.829 --> 01:22:17.389
including cigarettes, so that
one day, when they get older,

01:22:17.498 --> 01:22:19.329
they can choose for themselves.

01:22:21.569 --> 01:22:24.732
I look at my... son

01:22:24.839 --> 01:22:26.238
who...

01:22:26.340 --> 01:22:28.171
was kind enough
to come with me today,

01:22:28.275 --> 01:22:30.766
and I can't help but think

01:22:30.878 --> 01:22:33.142
that I am responsible
for his growth

01:22:33.247 --> 01:22:35.374
and his development.

01:22:35.483 --> 01:22:37.007
And I'm proud of that.

01:22:37.118 --> 01:22:38.380
Well, having
said that,

01:22:38.486 --> 01:22:41.046
would you condone him smoking?

01:22:41.155 --> 01:22:43.487
Well, of course not.
He's not 18.

01:22:43.591 --> 01:22:44.649
That would be illegal.

01:22:45.926 --> 01:22:48.019
<i>Yes, l-I heard you deliver</i>
<i>that line on <i>20-20,</i></i>

01:22:48.129 --> 01:22:49.494
but enough dancing.

01:22:49.597 --> 01:22:51.929
What are you going to do
when he turns 18?

01:22:53.601 --> 01:22:55.159
Come on, Mr. Naylor.

01:22:55.269 --> 01:22:58.830
On his 18th birthday, will
you share a cigarette with him?

01:22:58.939 --> 01:23:01.169
Will you spend
a lovely afternoon,

01:23:01.275 --> 01:23:03.436
like one of your ludicrous
cigarette advertisements?

01:23:03.544 --> 01:23:05.068
You seem to have a lot to say

01:23:05.179 --> 01:23:06.510
about how we
should raise our children.

01:23:06.614 --> 01:23:07.597
What of your own?

01:23:07.697 --> 01:23:10.149
What are you
going to do

01:23:10.251 --> 01:23:12.549
when he turns 18?

01:23:19.160 --> 01:23:22.823
If he really wants a cigarette,
I'll buy him his first pack.

01:23:27.568 --> 01:23:30.401
Thank you for your testimony,
Mr. Naylor. You're excused.

01:23:37.244 --> 01:23:38.677
I'll meet you outside, okay?

01:23:51.258 --> 01:23:52.816
Great.

01:23:52.927 --> 01:23:54.053
Well done, my boy.

01:23:54.161 --> 01:23:56.288
Were you in the same room as me?

01:23:56.397 --> 01:23:57.489
The whole personal choice thing?

01:23:57.598 --> 01:23:58.724
They ate that shit up.

01:23:58.833 --> 01:24:00.664
Just checked the whip count.

01:24:00.768 --> 01:24:02.167
That bill is going down in flames.

01:24:02.269 --> 01:24:05.102
Your speech was unorthodox,
but you did it, boy.

01:24:05.206 --> 01:24:06.156
You crushed the fucker.

01:24:06.256 --> 01:24:07.333
That's good news for you guys.

01:24:07.441 --> 01:24:08.840
Oh. Whoa, whoa.

01:24:08.943 --> 01:24:11.844
We're still a team, right?

01:24:11.946 --> 01:24:13.914
What about damage control?

01:24:15.416 --> 01:24:16.781
Look, Nick.

01:24:16.884 --> 01:24:20.479
Winston-Salem is ready
to do whatever it takes

01:24:20.588 --> 01:24:22.112
to keep you onboard.

01:24:30.364 --> 01:24:33.424
Nick, will you continue
fighting for cigarettes?

01:24:33.534 --> 01:24:34.865
Of course he will.

01:24:34.969 --> 01:24:36.937
This man here is our general.

01:24:37.037 --> 01:24:38.800
We're not just gonna let him retire.

01:24:38.906 --> 01:24:39.930
Is that correct, Nick?

01:24:40.040 --> 01:24:41.530
You're sticking with tobacco?

01:24:45.579 --> 01:24:49.071
<i>Now, I know what</i>
<i>you're probably thinking.</i>

01:24:49.183 --> 01:24:50.343
<i>What a great opportunity for me</i>

01:24:50.451 --> 01:24:52.043
<i>to teach Joey</i>
<i>how to use leverage against</i>

01:24:52.152 --> 01:24:53.744
<i>a backstabbing boss.</i>

01:24:53.854 --> 01:24:57.290
<i>But I actually meant what</i>
<i>I said about responsibility.</i>

01:24:57.391 --> 01:25:01.020
<i>Some things</i>
<i>are just more important</i>

01:25:01.128 --> 01:25:02.288
<i>than paying a mortgage.</i>

01:25:02.396 --> 01:25:04.990
<i>So I did the only responsible</i>
<i>thing I could.</i>

01:25:05.099 --> 01:25:07.863
<i>I turned down the job.</i>

01:25:07.968 --> 01:25:10.300
<i>And my timing</i>
<i>couldn't have been better.</i>

01:25:10.404 --> 01:25:12.702
<i>Within a few months,</i>
<i>the cigarette companies</i>

01:25:12.806 --> 01:25:14.205
<i>settled</i>
<i>with the American smoker</i>

01:25:14.308 --> 01:25:16.970
<i>to the tune of $246 billion.</i>

01:25:18.145 --> 01:25:20.477
<i>And the Academy</i>
<i>of Tobacco Studies</i>

01:25:20.581 --> 01:25:22.344
<i>was permanently dismantled.</i>

01:25:22.449 --> 01:25:24.747
<i>For the first time in decades,</i>

01:25:24.852 --> 01:25:26.547
<i>BR found himself out of work.</i>

01:25:28.322 --> 01:25:30.415
<i>Otherwise, not much has changed.</i>

01:25:30.524 --> 01:25:32.685
<i>The MOD squad still meets every week.</i>

01:25:32.793 --> 01:25:34.090
Nice.

01:25:34.194 --> 01:25:36.458
<i>We even added a few new members.</i>

01:25:36.563 --> 01:25:39.361
The things I could learn
from you, Bobby Jay.

01:25:39.466 --> 01:25:40.466
Right.

01:25:40.567 --> 01:25:42.000
Stick around. Stick around.

01:25:42.102 --> 01:25:44.832
<i>Senator Finistirre is still</i>
<i>fighting for his causes.</i>

01:25:44.939 --> 01:25:46.702
What do you say
to the people who claim

01:25:46.807 --> 01:25:48.741
you are destroying cinema classics?

01:25:48.842 --> 01:25:50.469
Mmm, no. All
we're doing

01:25:50.577 --> 01:25:52.238
is using
digital technology

01:25:52.346 --> 01:25:55.509
to tastefully update
movies of the past...

01:25:55.616 --> 01:25:57.174
by removing cigarettes.

01:25:57.284 --> 01:26:00.515
<i>I believe that if these</i>
<i>stars were alive today,</i>

01:26:00.621 --> 01:26:03.055
<i>they would agree that</i>
<i>we're doing the right thing.</i>

01:26:03.157 --> 01:26:04.886
But, in essence, aren't
you changing history?

01:26:04.992 --> 01:26:08.928
No, I think we're improving history.

01:26:10.798 --> 01:26:12.129
<i>Even Heather is still reporting.</i>

01:26:12.232 --> 01:26:13.597
The whole town has been evacuated.

01:26:13.701 --> 01:26:19.003
They're calling this
the storm of the century.

01:26:19.106 --> 01:26:20.437
<i>Not much changes at all.</i>

01:26:20.541 --> 01:26:25.240
And this year's Foggy Bottom
Debating Society Champion is...

01:26:25.346 --> 01:26:26.346
Joey Naylor.

01:26:26.447 --> 01:26:27.607
- Yay!
- Yay!

01:26:27.715 --> 01:26:28.665
Joey!

01:26:28.765 --> 01:26:29.666
Joey!

01:26:29.766 --> 01:26:30.667
Joey, Joey!

01:26:30.767 --> 01:26:32.242
That's my boy.

01:26:32.353 --> 01:26:33.911
Hold it up. Hold it up.

01:26:37.558 --> 01:26:39.583
<i>And me?</i>

01:26:39.693 --> 01:26:42.389
<i>Well, there's still a place</i>
<i>for guys like me.</i>

01:26:42.496 --> 01:26:45.124
So, be straight with me.

01:26:45.232 --> 01:26:47.962
Is it true?

01:26:48.068 --> 01:26:49.467
- It could be.
- Come on.

01:26:49.570 --> 01:26:51.663
We know of very few cases.

01:26:51.772 --> 01:26:52.898
There's no scientific proof at all.

01:26:53.007 --> 01:26:53.957
There was an unfortunate
incident out in Iowa...

01:26:54.057 --> 01:26:54.991
It's really a complicated situation.

01:26:55.091 --> 01:26:56.269
Gentlemen,

01:26:56.377 --> 01:26:58.971
practice these words
in front of the mirror.

01:26:59.079 --> 01:27:02.048
"Although we are constantly
exploring the subject,

01:27:02.149 --> 01:27:04.845
"currently,
there is no direct evidence

01:27:04.952 --> 01:27:06.351
"that links cell phone usage

01:27:06.453 --> 01:27:08.318
to brain cancer."

01:27:14.828 --> 01:27:16.625
<i>Michael Jordan plays ball.</i>

01:27:16.730 --> 01:27:18.288
<i>Charles Manson kills people.</i>

01:27:18.399 --> 01:27:19.866
<i>I talk.</i>

01:27:21.535 --> 01:27:22.661
<i>Everyone has a talent.</i>

